```gherkin
Feature: Training Options Display

  Scenario: Display training options with all required information
    Given I am an anonymous user on the training page
    When I view the training options
    Then I should see the day and time of training
    And I should see the title of the training
    And I should see a short summary of the training
    And I should see the trainers of the training
    And I should see the level of the training
    And I should see the number of registrations
    And I should see the remaining registrations
    And I should see the location of the training
    And I should see a link to full details of the training
    And I should see a "register now" link
```

```python
from behave import given, when, then

@given('I am an anonymous user on the training page')
def step_impl(context):
    context.browser.get('http://example.com/training')

@when('I view the training options')
def step_impl(context):
    context.training_options = context.browser.find_elements_by_class_name('training-option')

@then('I should see the day and time of training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-day-time').is_displayed()

@then('I should see the title of the training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-title').is_displayed()

@then('I should see a short summary of the training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-summary').is_displayed()

@then('I should see the trainers of the training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-trainers').is_displayed()

@then('I should see the level of the training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-level').is_displayed()

@then('I should see the number of registrations')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-registrations').is_displayed()

@then('I should see the remaining registrations')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-remaining-registrations').is_displayed()

@then('I should see the location of the training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-location').is_displayed()

@then('I should see a link to full details of the training')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-full-details-link').is_displayed()

@then('I should see a "register now" link')
def step_impl(context):
    for option in context.training_options:
        assert option.find_element_by_class_name('training-register-now-link').is_displayed()
```

Validation Checklist:
1. Verify the training page is accessible to anonymous users.
2. Verify the training options are displayed on the page.
3. Verify each training option displays the day and time of training.
4. Verify each training option displays the title of the training.
5. Verify each training option displays a short summary of the training.
